First Lady Melania Trump attended the 2019 VSA International Young Soloists Competition concert at the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. The concert showcased the talents of five young artists who performed two songs each. Melania Trump presented awards to each performer and joined them and their families at a reception. She emphasized the importance of music as a tool for communication and therapy and highlighted the significance of the arts in youth development. The event aligns with her Be Best initiative, which supports programs that boost youth confidence and encourage the exploration of passions. The performers were Tori Tedeschi Adams, Avery Dixon, Kasyfi Kalyasyena, Maya Wagner, and José André Montaño.